sequenceDiagram
    participant CLI as CLI / main
    participant API as API Layer
    participant IO as IO / VFS
    participant DEC as Decoder
    participant SCHED as Scheduler / Runtime
    participant GQ as Global Queue (MPMC)
    participant W as Worker Thread
    participant PIPE as Pipeline Executor (hot)
    participant JUMP as Jump Table
    participant ARCH as Arch Kernel (SIMD)
    participant ENC as Encoder
    participant FS as Filesystem / IO

    %% Normal path: file input -> decode -> submit -> execute -> encode
    CLI->>API: img_api_run_job(engine, input_path, output_path, job)
    API->>IO: open / mmap input file
    IO->>DEC: call g_io_vtable.decode(ctx, data, size, &photo)
    DEC-->>API: decoded img_buffer_t (photo)
    API->>SCHED: img_runtime_submit_task(task)
    SCHED->>GQ: push task (mpmc)
    W->>GQ: pop task (spsc fast-path then global mpmc)
    W->>PIPE: img_pipeline_execute_hot(ctx, compiled_pipeline, buffer)
    PIPE->>JUMP: for each op: fn = g_jump_table[op_code]
    JUMP->>ARCH: call kernel fn(ctx, buf, params)
    ARCH-->>PIPE: writes processed pixels into buffer
    W-->>API: task completed (status)
    API->>ENC: img_api_finish_job_output(ctx, canvas, layout, job)
    ENC->>FS: write output (io_uring or blocking write)
    FS-->>API: write complete
    API-->>CLI: return result

    %% Raw RGB24 ingress (decode-bypass)
    CLI->>API: img_api_run_job_rgb24_raw(engine, raw_rgb24, w,h,stride, job)
    API->>SCHED: submit prepared render task (no decode)
    SCHED->>W: schedule render stage
    W->>PIPE: execute hot pipeline (same as above)
    PIPE->>ENC: handoff to encoder (if required)

    %% Notes
    note over PIPE,JUMP: Jump table populated at startup (img_jump_table_init + hw registration)
    note over ARCH: Arch kernels are branchless, no allocations in hot path
